A man has been confirmed dead in an auto accident that occurred along Ipetu-Ijesa/Ilesa road on Thursday night. The fatal accident happened around 9:46 pm on Thursday, about 4 kilometres from Iwaraja Junction, Omo Ijesa, Osun State. It was gathered that a V/Wagen with registration number, FFA 889KA and a CNHTC truck with registration number DKA 374XA, crashed and claimed a life and left two others injured. The Sector Public Education Officer for Osun Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Agnes Ogungbemi said the victims have been taken by their relatives. She revealed that the team of FRSC left the scene due to the violence instigated by the victims’ relatives against the operatives. “Caution has been placed to notify the public on the danger ahead. The team left the scene due to the violence instigated by the victims’ relatives,” she said.